lysis, and information development needed to support the Secretary's responsibilities in the formulation of national transportation policies.
The program is carried out primarily through contracts with other Federal agencies, educational institutions, non-profit research organizations, and private firms.
Transportation policy and planning.--Activities support the development of transportation policy, coordination of national level transportation planning, and such issues as regulatory modernization, energy conservation, and environmental and safety impacts of transportation.
These also enable departmental leadership on aviation economic policy and international transportation issues.
Systems Development.--This activity funds system development of department-wide management systems.
In 2001, it includes resources to improve the Dockets management system.
