The Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended by TEAÂ­ 21, provides for the transfer of Highway Trust Fund revenue derived from the motor boat fuel tax and certain other taxes to the Aquatic Resources Trust Fund.
Appropriations are authorized from this fund to meet expenditures for programs specified by law, including sport fish restoration and boat safety.
Excise tax receipts for the trust fund include motorboat fuel tax receipts, plus receipts from taxes on sport fishing equipment, sonar and fish finders, and small engine fuel.
